  "notes": [
    "Category averages are calculated from populated canonical field counts divided by the submitted-domain denominator and the number of fields in each category.",
    "Returned-profile depth uses the average and median number of populated canonical fields on enriched records.",
    "ContactOut records were unwrapped from their dynamic top-level domain key before canonical field counting.",
    "CompanyEnrich uses the cleaned companyenrich.jsonl currently in the workspace.",
    "Country/state/city/street-or-full-address/postal-code are combined into one canonical location field.",
    "Placeholder values are treated as missing in canonical field coverage where applicable: numeric 0 for employee count, revenue, founded year, and follower count; and N/A-style strings for revenue.",
    "People Data Labs profiles[] is counted as Crunchbase only when the individual profile URL contains crunchbase.com.",
    "Website metadata/SEO metadata fields are excluded from the benchmark.",
    "Percentage columns in generated benchmark CSVs use the total submitted-domain denominator of 349; matched-record percentage columns preserve returned-record denominators where useful.",
    "The canonical 'domain' and 'website' fields were merged into a single 'domain_website' field because every tested provider populates the two fields from the same source path(s); counting them separately double-counted the same signal.",
    "The canonical 'multi_industries' field was removed because four of six tested providers mapped it to the same source path(s) as 'industry', which double-counted the same signal. Providers that genuinely return a multi-industry array (such as Apollo's industries[] or CompanyEnrich's industries[]) are still credited via 'industry'; the additional richness is not measured as a separate canonical field in this benchmark.",
    "Parent_company, subsidiaries, and affiliates were merged into a single 'corporate_relations' canonical field. For the only provider that exposed all three (PDL), the affiliates field was a near-superset of the other two, so treating them as three independent signals overstated org-structure depth. The combined field counts as present when any parent, subsidiary, or affiliate value was returned.",
    "Funding_rounds, total_funding, and funding_stage were merged into a single 'funding_data' canonical field. For every tested provider, 'any of these populated' equals the funding_rounds count exactly: stage and total are subsets of rounds. Counting them as three independent signals overstated funding coverage. The merged field counts as present when any rounds/stage/amount data was returned."
  ],
